replyContent: Thank you so much for the feedback and for supporting the project! It's a common request so we will try to include it with the next update. Thanks again!

content: The variety of exercises is awesome but it would be great to have a small animation to know how to perform the exercises.
replyContent: Thank you so much for the feedback and for supporting the resource! It's a good suggestion and we'll see if we can implement this in the future. In the meantime, we have a small video library here: http://darebee.com/exercises I hope this helps! And thanks again!

content: Does nothing
You can't select different body parts to train so is pretty pointless really.
I like the look of the workouts, but just displaying a sheet of exorcises to do, is useful on a small screen. So being able to see what you should be doing or counting down etc..  Is far to manual.
replyContent:
Thank you so much for the feedback! We will try to improve the app when we can (money is an issue, hence this fundraising). The app is basic but if you do like the routines perhaps the manual from the resource can be of help: http://darebee.com/manual I hope this helps.

Thank you for supporting us, we appreciate it!

content: No energy calculator
Awesome app :P
would like to see some animations or descriptions to the exercises. both would be perfect

If you only expect apps to be an awkwardly sorted collection of jpeg files with a horrible and dated UI then you will be pleased with this app. If you expect apps to be more than a lazily put together piece of junk then give this one a miss. There has been no effort made to format the workouts for small screens, there are no animations of the workouts and practically no interactively. There is so much potential here but unfortunately the developer has just lazily created a lacklustre image browsing utility.
replyContent: We are really sorry we made you feel frustrated. As you pointed out, it is a very simple app but we cannot afford to make it any better at this time, DAREBEE is a struggling non-profit & the app is our way of raising the funds to continue our work at darebee.com. You should be able to get a full refund but if not, please let us know & we'll help.

content: It's a good pocket guide to workout routines, but it needs a 'favourites' shortlist and the option to play a random workout from the favourites list. After that, some more detailed instructions for the exercises would be great, along with a little graphic to show what muscles each exercise targets.
replyContent: Thank you so much for the feedback and for supporting the resource! We hope to be able to afford to add more features in the future. Thank you, again.

content: Poorly illustrated workouts. No workouts including any form of weight training, which is absolutely useless for me. Refunded.
replyContent: We are really sorry you feel that way and we apologize for not making it clearer that this is a bodyweight collection. We will fix the description asap. In the meantime you are welcome to any of our workouts at darebee.com. It's mostly circuit training but it's all free. This app is for fund raising only and DAREBEE is a non-profit resource.

content: Champion for making these! Definitely a motivation booster! Thanks
